      "text": "\"The large investment in e-learning has made user acceptance an increasingly critical issue for technology implementation and management (Ong, Lai, &Wang, 2004). Among educational technology users, educators form the large majority as they act as drivers in the effective integration of technology for teaching and learning (Teo, Lee, Chai, & Wong, 2009). Studies have shown that the successful implementation of educational technologies depends largely on the attitudes and acceptance of educators (Sanchez-Franco et al., 2009; Yuen & Ma, 2008). Thus, <strong>educational institutions should make efforts to encourage instructor use and ensure instructor satisfaction for the successful adoption of web-based learning systems (Wang &Wang, 2009)</strong>.\" (p. 169)"
    },
